    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The y-axis matches the direction of gravity as detected by the device’s motion sensing hardware; that is, the vector ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "(0,-1,0)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " points downward.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The position and orientation of the device as of when the session configuration is first run determine the rest of the coordinate system: For the z-axis, ARKit chooses a basis vector ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "(0,0,-1)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " pointing in the direction the device camera faces and perpendicular to the gravity axis. ARKit chooses a x-axis based on the z- and y-axes using the right hand rule—that is, the basis vector ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "(1,0,0)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is orthogonal to the other two axes, and (for a viewer looking in the negative-z direction) points toward the right.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "media-2891463",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
